# Bootstrap is a free, open-source front-end framework that helps developers build responsive, mobile-first websites quickly using prebuilt HTML, CSS, and JavaScript components.
 It’s widely used because it simplifies design with ready-made styles, a powerful grid system, and interactive elements like modals, carousels, and dropdowns.
